.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-6-4::.
4 different games are played: poker, canasta, backgammon, scrabble
The people use 4 different means of transport: quad-bike, subway, train, trike
1. the person playing backgammon is on the left of the person playing scrabble##1
2. the person playing canasta is somewhere to the left of the person driving the quad-bike##5
3. the person driving the trike is not the person playing canasta##6
4. the person driving the trike is somewhere to the right of the person driving the quad-bike##5
5. the person driving the train is on the right of the person driving the subway##1
6. the person playing scrabble is somewhere to the left of the person driving the trike##5

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |    2     |     3     |    4     |
| Pet         | canasta | backgammon | scrabble     | poker |
| Transport   | subway     | train    | quad-bike | trike    |

